The paper deals with compressive sensing and sparse signal recovery, which are topics typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT), Signal Processing (cs.SP), and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of free random matrices, which includes Haar matrices and other unitarily invariant matrices, is a key aspect of the paper and is likely to be of interest to researchers in the Matrix Methods (cs.MM) and Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) sub-categories.
